co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.lib
Interface TimePartitionedFileSet

All Superinterfaces:
Closeable, Dataset, InputFormatProvider, OutputFormatProvider
@Beta
public interface TimePartitionedFileSet
extends Dataset, InputFormatProvider, OutputFormatProvider

Represents a dataset that is split into partitions that can be uniquely addressed by time. Each partition is a path in a file set, with a timestamp attached as meta data. This dataset can be made available for querying with SQL (explore). This is enabled through dataset properties when the dataset is created. See FileSetProperties for details. If it is enabled for explore, a Hive external table will be created when the dataset is created. The Hive table is partitioned by year, month, day, hour and minute.
